'''Iupiter''' (dal latin ''Iovem'', accusatif de ''Iuppiter'') y cun referimënt al inom de Zeus (tl grech antich Ζεύς), le pere dles divinités tla mitologia greca, é le cuinto [[Planet|planët]] dl [[Sistem soler|Sistem solar]] en cunt de destanza dal [[Suredl|Sorëdl]] y le plü gran de döt le sistem di planëc. Süa massa è dui iadi y mez tan gran respet a chëra de düc i atri planëc adöm<ref>George H. A. Cole e Michael M. Woolfson, ''Planetary Science: The Science of Planets Around Stars'', CRC Press, 2002, p. 68, ISBN 978-0-7503-0815-1</ref>. Adöm cun [[Saturn]], [[Uran]] y [[Netun]] él classifiché sicöche “gigant de gas”.
[[File:Jupiter and its shrunken Great Red Spot.jpg|thumb|Jupiter]]
Süa composiziun ti somëia a chëra dl Sorëdl, cun idrogen, elio, amoniaca, ega y metan. Al vëgn araté che so nucleus sides metü adöm da crëp cun carbonium y silicac de fer curis da n mantel de idrogen metalich y na atmosfera<ref>T Guillot, ''A comparison of the interiors of Jupiter and Saturn'', te ''Planetary and Space Science'', vol. 47, 10–11, 1999, pl. 1183–200, DOI:10.1016/S0032-0633(99)00043-4</ref> cun presciuns dër altes<ref> Linda T. Elkins-Tanton, Jupiter and Saturn, New York, Chelsea House, 2006, ISBN 0-8160-5196-8.</ref>. Le corú dl’atmosfera esterna, che é metüda adöm por le 88-92% da idrogen molecolar y da n 8-12% de elio<ref> Linda T. Elkins-Tanton, ''Jupiter and Saturn'', New York, Chelsea House, 2006, ISBN 0-8160-5196-8.</ref>, vá dal ross lominus al ross cun chëra che vëgn nominada “Gran Tacia Cöcena<ref>A. P. Ingersoll, T. E. Dowling, P. J. Gierasch, et al, ''Dynamics of Jupiter's Atmosphere'' (PDF), Lunar & Planetary Institute.</ref>.
Iupiter é le cuarto corp dl cil plü slominant do le Sorëdl, la [[Löna]] y Venus<ref> Peter J. Gierasch, Philip D. Nicholson, Jupiter, World Book @ NASA, 2004.</ref>.

Le sistem d’aní de Iupiter é metü adöm dantadöt da silicac. Ai aní plü esterns ti vëgnel dit “aní Gossamer” <ref> L. W. Esposito, ''Planetary rings'', te ''Reports On Progress In Physics'', vol. 65, 2002, pp. 1741–1783, DOI:10.1088/0034-4885/65/12/201</ref>. Atualmënter él gnü identifiché 79 satelic naturai de Iupiter<ref>Jupiter's Moons: 12 More Found, 79 Known - Sky & Telescope, su Sky & Telescope, 17 luglio 2018.</ref>.

Dal 1973 inant él gnü a se le dé deplü surajors (fly-by) de Iupiter cun sondes: la ''Pioneer 10'' y dl 1974 la ''Pioneer 11''<ref> Eric Burgess, ''By Jupiter: Odysseys to a Giant'', New York, Columbia University Press, 1982, ISBN 0-231-05176-X.</ref>.
